channel.title: CVE Feed for Dell -- RSA Archer
channel.description: The latest CVEs for Dell -- RSA Archer

item.title: CVE-2020-5335|2024-08-04T08:30:23.322Z -- dell -- rsa%20archer
item.description: RSA Archer, versions prior to 6.7 P2 (6.7.0.2), contain a cross-site request forgery vulnerability. A remote unauthenticated attacker could potentially exploit this vulnerability by tricking a victim application user to send arbitrary requests to the vulnerable application to perform server operations with the privileges of the authenticated victim user.

item.title: CVE-2020-5331|2024-08-04T08:30:23.302Z -- dell -- rsa%20archer
item.description: RSA Archer, versions prior to 6.7 P3 (6.7.0.3), contain an information exposure vulnerability. Usersâ€™ session information could potentially be stored in cache or log files. An authenticated malicious local user with access to the log files may obtain the exposed information to use it in further attacks.

item.title: CVE-2020-5332|2024-08-04T08:30:22.869Z -- dell -- rsa%20archer
item.description: RSA Archer, versions prior to 6.7 P3 (6.7.0.3), contain a command injection vulnerability. AN authenticated malicious user with administrator privileges could potentially exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary commands on the system where the vulnerable application is deployed.

item.title: CVE-2020-5334|2024-08-04T08:30:22.832Z -- dell -- rsa%20archer
item.description: RSA Archer, versions prior to 6.7 P2 (6.7.0.2), contains a Document Object Model (DOM) based cross-site scripting vulnerability. A remote unauthenticated attacker could potentially exploit this vulnerability by tricking a victim application user to supply malicious HTML or JavaScript code to DOM environment in the browser. The malicious code is then executed by the web browser in the context of the vulnerable web application.

item.title: CVE-2020-5333|2024-08-04T08:30:22.853Z -- dell -- rsa%20archer
item.description: RSA Archer, versions prior to 6.7 P3 (6.7.0.3), contain an authorization bypass vulnerability in the REST API. A remote authenticated malicious Archer user could potentially exploit this vulnerability to view unauthorized information.

item.title: CVE-2020-5337|2024-08-04T08:30:23.284Z -- dell -- rsa%20archer
item.description: RSA Archer, versions prior to 6.7 P1 (6.7.0.1), contain a URL redirection vulnerability. A remote unauthenticated attacker could potentially exploit this vulnerability to redirect application users to arbitrary web URLs by tricking the victim users to click on maliciously crafted links. The vulnerability could be used to conduct phishing attacks that cause users to unknowingly visit malicious sites.

item.title: CVE-2020-5336|2024-08-04T08:30:22.830Z -- dell -- rsa%20archer
item.description: RSA Archer, versions prior to 6.7 P1 (6.7.0.1), contain a URL injection vulnerability. An unauthenticated attacker could potentially exploit this vulnerability by tricking a victim application user to execute malicious JavaScript code on the affected system.
